<TEXTAREA NAME="ReplyMessage" ROWS=10 COLS=45 WRAP="VIRTUAL">[QUOTE]Originally posted by Atro:
[B]I wish I had time to read this entire thread, all three pages of it.  However I don't, I guess I'm a casual board camper, and as such this comment may be outdated.  However what I do see here is this:  

Rayne's system is not designed to be fair.  It's not designed to make people happy.  Rayne's post is actually a quest spoiler.  Just not everyone sees it as such.

This is the quest:
Sometime between 0 and 72 hours after a known event (naggy/previous Zordakalicious is killed) a trigger event will occur (Zordak will spawn).  When that trigger event occurs you must turn in a shimmering pearl (obtained in a different quest), then kill one mob which is triggerd and upon dying triggers another mob.  Kill that mob to recieve an item, which when turned in gives you the holy bonker of make your dead friends come back naked and in pain.  However you must accomplish this task before the immanant attack by some group that you don't beling to occurs.  This attack may come within minutes or not for hours, it is random (not unlike the timing on the trigger event).  If you do not acomplish your goal before this attack occurs you have failed, and must start this quest over (note not necessarily the other quest which results in the shimmering pearl).  If you succeed congradulations.  If you fail, prepair more and better luck next time.

There it is.

Sound's harsh?  Well, VI didn't create this quest, they only created the foundation upon which this quest came into being.  They are unwilling to alter he foundation regardles of their opinion on the quest that was built on it.  We created this quest, but look on the bright side, Rayne was kind enough to give you the spoiler.  Like any other quest spoiler, you can choose to ignore it, but if you fail, you have noone to blame but yourself.

This is the way EQ is right now.  This may never change, though it might.  When the second cleric in my guild completed this quest this is exactly how he did it.  If I could I would have done it the same way.  It was actually kinda fun.  I wasn't there for the entire 72+ hours he spent, but there were people there for that long.  However a force sufficient or nearly so to complete this quest was there most of the time, with just small times during a sort of changing of the guards ocured.  This does not have to be a boring camp either.  We pulled EL to Naggy's lair and AE'd.  I personally witnessed a Tranix crown and GEBs drop in ONE pull.  I earned Exp, perople got loot (Though not much to be had as a cleric there if you're like me and believe GEBs are for pyjamas =P).  I saw a group of 5 clerics KS mobs from a group of 3 wizards a cleric chanter and war.  

I am envious of the support that cleric had.  To have so many people there, giving so much.  I have not earned that much within the guild or server comminuty, and may never.  I was lucky, I completed the above quest the hard way.  But like I said I was lucky, Zordak spawned about 16hours after the previos Zodakalicious died.  This was back when we all had theories like 24 hours after Naggy/previous Zordakalicious dies the next will spawn.  I thought that the spawn would occur at 8am my time, about an hour before a planned ToV raid.  I was afraid I would have to ask the guild to delay their ToV raid to help me bring down the beast.  I was lucky Zordak spawned for me 4 hours eairly, and my friends came pouring in faster than the attack by other forces occured and I succeded in this quest.  Since then I've seen or helped people doing this quest in a number of occasions.

Out dated and off topic?  Maybe, but I for one have to say, "Thank you Rayne, for giving us this quest spoiler so we now know how to complete this quest."

For those of you who decide to undertake this quest, I wish you luck.  For those of you who wish to undertake some other quest with the same reward, unless you are in the right community that quest may not exist, and you need to accept that.  I'm sympathetic to your plight, but there is nothing I can do for you.

-Atro Demerzel, cleric of The Companions on the Tribunal.[/B][/QUOTE]

</TEXTAREA>
